<quickviewtext name="Quick View">
<![CDATA[
<p>Have you ever wondered what your stuff is made of? Cell phones, semiconductors, automobiles, airplanes, tennis rackets, bicycles, Space Shuttle tiles, and surgical implants—all of these objects rely on metals, ceramics, glasses, or polymers. Discovering new materials and integrating them into engineering design is the heart of the <span class="title-main">Materials Science &amp; Engineering </span>discipline.</p>
